WEBVTT

00:01:34.039 --> 00:01:36.360
Flight control is my second home.

00:01:37.680 --> 00:01:38.920
You are all my family.

00:02:29.600 --> 00:02:30.960
Don't worry about me.

00:02:31.400 --> 00:02:32.600
Wait for me to return.

00:02:42.880 --> 00:02:44.480
Here they come.

00:02:52.320 --> 00:02:53.579
Let's give them a hand.

00:02:57.360 --> 00:02:58.000
What are you waiting for?

00:02:58.000 --> 00:02:58.960
Get the luggage.

00:02:58.960 --> 00:02:59.520
Hello.

00:02:59.520 --> 00:03:00.360
You must be Mr. Yan.

00:03:00.360 --> 00:03:01.040
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:03:01.040 --> 00:03:02.040
Don't.

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:02.800
How was the trip?

00:03:02.800 --> 00:03:04.720
You must be tired from the long journey.

00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:05.780
I'm fine, I'm fine.

00:03:05.880 --> 00:03:07.740
I'll be troubling you from now on.

00:03:08.200 --> 00:03:09.800
Not at all.

00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:11.040
Hello, hello.

00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:12.040
Hello, Wu Wei.

00:03:12.440 --> 00:03:13.280
Luggage.

00:03:13.440 --> 00:03:14.440
No, thanks. I can handle it.

00:03:14.440 --> 00:03:15.080
I can handle it.

00:03:15.080 --> 00:03:16.160
Don't call me teacher.

00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:17.160
Just call me Lao Yan.

00:03:17.160 --> 00:03:18.960
It's different here from Beijing.

00:03:18.960 --> 00:03:20.640
We don't do that 'teacher' stuff.

00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:22.160
In Kashgar, in Yangdaman,

00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:23.520
there aren't so many rules

00:03:23.520 --> 00:03:24.520
or nonsense.

00:03:24.520 --> 00:03:25.560
From now on, I'll call you Lao Zhang,

00:03:25.560 --> 00:03:26.760
and I'll call you Lao Wu.

00:03:26.760 --> 00:03:27.760
Xiao Wu.

00:03:27.760 --> 00:03:28.560
Xiao Wu.

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:30.700
Xiao Wu is fine too.

00:03:31.640 --> 00:03:33.120
Must be a tough trip here.

00:03:33.120 --> 00:03:33.680
After arriving in Kashgar,

00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.520
it takes another three or four hours by car to get here.

00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:36.880
Everyone knew you were coming

00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:37.920
and they were so happy.

00:03:37.920 --> 00:03:39.560
In the middle of nowhere like this,

00:03:39.560 --> 00:03:41.400
we rarely see new faces.

00:03:41.400 --> 00:03:43.320
You two are as rare as giant pandas.

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:44.280
To be honest,

00:03:44.280 --> 00:03:46.880
the environment here is much better than I imagined.

00:03:46.880 --> 00:03:47.600
Of course.

00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:49.360
The facilities are getting better and better.

00:03:49.360 --> 00:03:50.480
We have everything we need.

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:51.200
Rest assured.

00:03:51.200 --> 00:03:53.400
You two definitely won't suffer in your daily life.

00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:55.120
Come on, let's talk as we walk.

00:03:56.320 --> 00:03:58.160
I'm mainly in charge of the equipment team,

00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:00.200
from antenna maintenance to the power distribution room.

00:04:00.200 --> 00:04:01.280
Sometimes when we're short on hands,

00:04:01.280 --> 00:04:02.810
I also double as logistics.

00:04:02.840 --> 00:04:03.520
So,

00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:05.280
feel free to come to me if you need anything.

00:04:05.280 --> 00:04:07.360
I promise the service will be spot on.

00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:08.520
Let's put it this way.

00:04:08.520 --> 00:04:10.640
Our place may be small, but it's fully equipped.

00:04:10.640 --> 00:04:11.500
Hello, Old Yan.

00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:13.800
Our area is not large, but the responsibility is heavy.

00:04:13.800 --> 00:04:15.960
We are the first station for China's aerospace tracking and control,

00:04:15.960 --> 00:04:16.880
the western gate of tracking and control.

00:04:16.880 --> 00:04:18.120
We must guard this pass well.

00:04:18.120 --> 00:04:18.680
Yes.

00:04:19.079 --> 00:04:19.920
Come in.

00:04:19.920 --> 00:04:20.560
Okay, come in.

00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:21.600
Come in.

00:04:23.640 --> 00:04:24.080
Come on.

00:04:24.080 --> 00:04:25.280
Right here, this way.

00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:27.840
Come in.

00:04:28.440 --> 00:04:28.960
Come on.

00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:31.720
Everyone, put down your work for a moment.

00:04:31.720 --> 00:04:32.880
Let me introduce to you,

00:04:32.880 --> 00:04:34.159
experts from Beijing.

00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:37.600
Zhang Ziming from the Institute of Space Technology.

00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:39.640
This is Wu Wei from the Flight Control Department.

00:04:39.640 --> 00:04:41.920
They were specially seconded here

00:04:41.920 --> 00:04:43.200
to help us complete

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:45.360
the R&D and testing of the deep space array.

00:04:45.360 --> 00:04:45.920
Welcome.

00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:56.080
For the development work of this part,

00:04:56.080 --> 00:04:57.520
I will take the lead from now on.

00:04:57.520 --> 00:04:59.250
I won't say more pleasantries.

00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:01.880
We are only one step away from success.

00:05:02.560 --> 00:05:03.760
So I hope

00:05:03.760 --> 00:05:05.160
everyone will work hard together

00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:06.890
to finish building this array.

00:05:09.240 --> 00:05:10.680
I am just a newcomer.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:11.880
I am here

00:05:12.040 --> 00:05:13.760
to learn from all of you.

00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:15.820
Please give me your guidance.

00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:18.720
China Aerospace.

00:05:21.120 --> 00:05:22.050
Everyone knows.

00:05:22.520 --> 00:05:24.080
To improve the deep space TT&C network's

00:05:24.080 --> 00:05:25.160
data reception capabilities

00:05:25.160 --> 00:05:27.120
and improve the signal-to-noise ratio of signal synthesis,

00:05:27.120 --> 00:05:28.720
we developed a system software

00:05:28.720 --> 00:05:31.320
that integrates signal synthesis, demodulation,

00:05:31.320 --> 00:05:34.600
and data processing.

00:05:35.080 --> 00:05:36.740
With the needs of the mission,

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:39.520
our requirements for data transmission speed

00:05:39.520 --> 00:05:41.040
and synthesis accuracy

00:05:41.040 --> 00:05:42.170
are getting higher.

00:05:44.880 --> 00:05:46.800
But we don't have much time.

00:05:46.800 --> 00:05:49.200
I hope everyone can fully cooperate.

00:05:53.080 --> 00:05:53.610
Mr. Dong.

00:05:53.720 --> 00:05:54.360
Go ahead.

00:05:55.320 --> 00:05:56.440
We've already read some of the rendezvous

00:05:56.440 --> 00:05:58.570
and docking materials on the way here.

00:05:58.640 --> 00:06:00.160
We have also made some backup plans

00:06:00.160 --> 00:06:01.640
for the accuracy of the capture system.

00:06:01.640 --> 00:06:02.480
We can all discuss it

00:06:02.480 --> 00:06:03.560
together later.

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:05.040
That's great.

00:06:06.120 --> 00:06:06.840
Honestly,

00:06:06.840 --> 00:06:08.040
you two have worked so hard.

00:06:08.040 --> 00:06:08.760
Since you arrived,

00:06:08.760 --> 00:06:10.480
we haven't even properly hosted you.

00:06:10.480 --> 00:06:11.080
It's fine.

00:06:11.280 --> 00:06:12.940
We are here to solve problems.

00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:13.960
Right.

00:06:13.960 --> 00:06:16.320
You can host us however you want after the mission is completed.

00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:17.560
I heard from Mr. Zhang

00:06:17.560 --> 00:06:19.120
that the Yangrou Paomo here is pretty good.

00:06:19.120 --> 00:06:20.640
No problem. All you can eat.

00:06:20.640 --> 00:06:21.240
By the way,

00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:23.160
These two workstations are prepared for you.

00:06:23.160 --> 00:06:24.600
Let's communicate anytime if you have any questions.

00:06:24.600 --> 00:06:25.440
Okay.

00:06:25.960 --> 00:06:27.420
Thanks for your hard work.

00:06:38.680 --> 00:06:40.400
How is the plan I asked you to debug?

00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:41.840
No problem. Let's start the test.

00:06:41.840 --> 00:06:42.440
Okay.

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:00.440
How is it?

00:07:04.640 --> 00:07:05.440
Not ideal.

00:07:05.520 --> 00:07:07.380
Be specific. What's the problem?

00:07:10.720 --> 00:07:13.560
The sampling algorithm processing needs adjustment.

00:07:13.560 --> 00:07:15.280
There might also be a problem with spectrum synthesis.

00:07:15.280 --> 00:07:16.480
I don't want options.

00:07:16.480 --> 00:07:17.480
I want judgments.

00:07:17.720 --> 00:07:19.320
What exactly is the problem?

00:07:22.640 --> 00:07:24.000
I'm not quite sure yet.

00:07:24.320 --> 00:07:25.850
Then what can you be sure of?

00:07:32.240 --> 00:07:32.880
Wu Wei,

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:36.080
we will be working together here for a long time.

00:07:36.080 --> 00:07:37.400
I'll put it out there right now.

00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:38.360
I hope you can understand

00:07:38.360 --> 00:07:39.440
why you went to such great lengths to come here.

00:07:39.440 --> 00:07:40.700
What exactly is it for?

00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:41.720
If it's just because

00:07:41.720 --> 00:07:43.680
you don't want to stay in routine monitoring

00:07:43.680 --> 00:07:45.880
and want to come here to coast and get task experience,

00:07:45.880 --> 00:07:46.720
then I advise you

00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:48.200
to go back right now.

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:50.320
I don't keep idle hands here.

00:07:55.560 --> 00:07:56.520
When do you want it?

00:07:56.520 --> 00:07:58.580
That depends on when you can deliver.

00:08:03.640 --> 00:08:04.320
Tomorrow.

00:08:05.240 --> 00:08:06.040
I can deliver it tomorrow.

00:08:06.040 --> 00:08:06.800
Are you sure?

00:08:08.520 --> 00:08:09.160
I am sure.

00:08:09.880 --> 00:08:10.520
Okay.

00:08:18.040 --> 00:08:20.040
I believe the emergency collision avoidance plan

00:08:20.040 --> 00:08:21.280
can completely resolve

00:08:21.280 --> 00:08:24.840
the concerns raised by the expert just now.

00:08:24.840 --> 00:08:25.640
Dr. Chu.

00:08:25.640 --> 00:08:26.520
But we understand that

00:08:26.520 --> 00:08:30.640
your country's Zhengtu-5B carrier rocket

00:08:30.640 --> 00:08:32.280
is the heaviest

00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:34.120
self-returning spacecraft in the last thirty years.

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:35.120
We highly doubt whether China

00:08:35.120 --> 00:08:39.200
has the capability to handle space debris.

00:08:46.200 --> 00:08:48.560
Our Zhengtu-5B carrier rocket

00:08:48.560 --> 00:08:51.240
adopts internationally accepted practices.

00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:53.240
Its final stage has been passivated

00:08:53.240 --> 00:08:56.600
to ensure it will not explode in orbit.

00:08:56.600 --> 00:08:59.320
During reentry into the atmosphere,

00:08:59.320 --> 00:09:03.880
space debris will also be ablated and destroyed.

00:09:04.760 --> 00:09:09.360
The risk caused to aviation activities and the ground

00:09:09.360 --> 00:09:10.800
is extremely low.

00:09:11.040 --> 00:09:12.960
But I also want to say that some media,

00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:13.960
and some people on this issue...

00:09:13.960 --> 00:09:15.960
There is clearly a double standard.

00:09:18.440 --> 00:09:19.760
You may still remember

00:09:19.760 --> 00:09:22.720
when the rocket debris from the International Aerospace Development Technology Company

00:09:22.720 --> 00:09:24.880
fell onto a local farm.

00:09:26.200 --> 00:09:29.640
Some said it was a romantic meteor shooting across the night sky,

00:09:29.640 --> 00:09:34.120
a dazzling light show.

00:09:40.680 --> 00:09:43.120
We are willing to work with everyone here,

00:09:43.120 --> 00:09:44.320
as well as more countries,

00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:48.640
to strengthen cooperation in the aerospace field,

00:09:48.640 --> 00:09:50.680
but we firmly oppose

00:09:50.680 --> 00:09:53.320
holding a double standard on this issue.

00:09:53.320 --> 00:09:54.360
In fact,

00:09:54.360 --> 00:09:57.840
since our country launched its first artificial satellite,

00:09:57.840 --> 00:09:59.720
for over sixty years,

00:09:59.720 --> 00:10:01.960
there has never been

00:10:01.960 --> 00:10:04.440
a case of rocket debris hitting a person.

00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:07.160
I think everyone here is a professional,

00:10:07.160 --> 00:10:12.000
and we shouldn't over-exaggerate or create panic.

00:10:23.160 --> 00:10:24.290
You seem quite free.

00:10:24.840 --> 00:10:26.570
Are you done with the proposal?

00:10:31.920 --> 00:10:33.050
Why is there so much?

00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:34.680
I re-screened

00:10:34.680 --> 00:10:36.360
all the possible problem areas.

00:10:36.360 --> 00:10:38.200
These are basically confirmed.

00:10:38.400 --> 00:10:39.800
Confirmed is confirmed.

00:10:39.880 --> 00:10:41.880
There is no 'basically confirmed'.

00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:44.800
You throw this pile of stuff at me,

00:10:44.800 --> 00:10:46.530
expecting me to choose for you?

00:10:48.920 --> 00:10:49.680
Got it.

00:10:49.920 --> 00:10:51.360
I'll continue to optimize and troubleshoot.

00:10:51.360 --> 00:10:52.240
Just say it.

00:10:52.720 --> 00:10:54.080
I gave you these plans

00:10:54.240 --> 00:10:55.640
to discuss them with you.

00:10:56.040 --> 00:10:57.370
Communication is fine.

00:10:57.840 --> 00:10:59.120
But I hope our communication

00:10:59.120 --> 00:11:00.000
is effective.

00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:02.560
Not you throwing all these problems at me

00:11:02.560 --> 00:11:03.840
for me to solve.

00:11:05.400 --> 00:11:06.680
You need to know

00:11:06.680 --> 00:11:07.840
I'm not Chu Jiajia.

00:11:08.080 --> 00:11:09.480
And you're not an intern.

00:11:09.840 --> 00:11:11.600
If something goes wrong here, no one will cover for you.

00:11:11.600 --> 00:11:12.400
Mr. Zhang,

00:11:12.800 --> 00:11:14.440
I accept your criticism.

00:11:14.720 --> 00:11:16.720
But there's no need to bring Jia into this.

00:11:16.720 --> 00:11:18.840
What, am I wrong?

00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:25.080
I'll sort out the exact plan.

00:11:26.120 --> 00:11:27.240
I'll give it to you tonight.

00:11:27.240 --> 00:11:27.960
Wait.

00:11:29.240 --> 00:11:30.240
Hardware system,

00:11:30.640 --> 00:11:32.440
algorithm delay compensation,

00:11:33.240 --> 00:11:34.370
and plan synthesis.

00:11:35.080 --> 00:11:36.640
Take these three back to work on.

00:11:36.640 --> 00:11:37.840
I'll handle the rest.

00:11:39.480 --> 00:11:41.280
I'll give you a little more time.

00:11:42.240 --> 00:11:43.900
Can you give it to me this week?

00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:46.040
Yes.

00:11:48.040 --> 00:11:48.640
Okay.

00:12:06.720 --> 00:12:07.720
Good job, Jiajia.

00:12:09.760 --> 00:12:11.200
You are amazing, Sister Jia.

00:12:11.200 --> 00:12:12.680
Don't pay attention to them.

00:12:12.680 --> 00:12:13.680
After all these years,

00:12:13.680 --> 00:12:15.200
they are still using the same trick,

00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:16.320
bullying the few with the many,

00:12:16.320 --> 00:12:18.080
without any progress.

00:12:18.560 --> 00:12:20.160
You are awesome, Sister Jia.

00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:21.400
Especially that sentence,

00:12:21.400 --> 00:12:23.360
The internet has a memory.

00:12:24.040 --> 00:12:25.680
That was simply great.

00:12:34.280 --> 00:12:36.010
Thanks for your hard work, Jia.

00:13:28.600 --> 00:13:29.600
Hello, Mr. Gu.

00:13:29.880 --> 00:13:30.640
Jiajia.

00:13:30.720 --> 00:13:31.840
I saw the news.

00:13:31.840 --> 00:13:33.960
I've already reported it to the higher-ups.

00:13:33.960 --> 00:13:36.620
They will make a corresponding statement soon.

00:13:37.600 --> 00:13:38.600
Okay, Mr. Gu.

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:39.480
I will

00:13:39.480 --> 00:13:41.960
sort out the meeting minutes and send them to you later.

00:13:41.960 --> 00:13:42.640
By the way,

00:13:42.640 --> 00:13:44.680
I have another meeting tomorrow.

00:13:44.680 --> 00:13:46.080
I will communicate with them

00:13:46.080 --> 00:13:48.280
about the deep space cooperation plan.

00:13:50.320 --> 00:13:51.800
As for the specific details,

00:13:51.800 --> 00:13:53.660
I'll contact you again tomorrow.

00:13:54.440 --> 00:13:55.000
Okay.

00:13:55.400 --> 00:13:57.360
We will also respond to the international remarks

00:13:57.360 --> 00:14:00.040
and make corresponding statements and feedback.

00:14:00.040 --> 00:14:01.120
Thank you for your hard work, Jiajia.

00:14:01.120 --> 00:14:02.250
Get some rest early.

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:03.800
Okay, Mr. Gu.

00:14:19.240 --> 00:14:20.970
Thanks for your hard work, Jia.

00:14:25.360 --> 00:14:28.640
Jia, I saw the video of your speech abroad.

00:14:29.200 --> 00:14:29.840
Let's just say,

00:14:29.840 --> 00:14:31.480
isn't it a bit too much?

00:14:31.480 --> 00:14:32.920
You literally took on a group of scholars

00:14:32.920 --> 00:14:34.480
and crushed them all the way.

00:14:34.480 --> 00:14:35.760
I suggest that before your next speech,

00:14:35.760 --> 00:14:38.000
you buy some insurance for those foreigners.

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:39.760
With such a high density of knowledge,

00:14:39.760 --> 00:14:41.320
can they handle it?

00:14:42.760 --> 00:14:45.960
You must have stayed up late a lot for the speech, Jia.

00:14:45.960 --> 00:14:47.640
Now use the method I taught you immediately

00:14:47.640 --> 00:14:48.560
to stretch a bit,

00:14:48.560 --> 00:14:50.560
so your backache won't act up again.

00:14:50.640 --> 00:14:52.240
Even if Muxingren are tough,

00:14:52.440 --> 00:14:53.560
you can't really

00:14:53.560 --> 00:14:55.480
treat yourself like a spinning top every day.

00:14:55.480 --> 00:14:57.720
I'm watching your daily step count.

00:14:57.720 --> 00:14:59.920
I will check in and supervise you regularly.

00:14:59.920 --> 00:15:02.480
Health supervisor Wu is now online.

00:15:02.960 --> 00:15:04.240
Seriously, Jia,

00:15:04.240 --> 00:15:07.100
take care of yourself. Waiting for you to come back.

00:15:09.160 --> 00:15:10.880
Chu Jiajia, remember this.

00:15:11.120 --> 00:15:12.000
Flight control work

00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:14.130
isn't just about calculating orbits.

00:15:14.200 --> 00:15:17.040
It's also about ensuring the safe operation of the spacecraft.

00:15:17.040 --> 00:15:19.520
There's no room for luck in space missions.

00:15:20.200 --> 00:15:22.200
This is your first return-to-zero.

00:15:22.280 --> 00:15:24.210
Although Mr. Qin didn't blame you,

00:15:24.400 --> 00:15:27.040
you must learn your lesson.

00:15:46.080 --> 00:15:47.480
Lao Yan, it's me.

00:15:49.160 --> 00:15:50.640
I want to confirm something with you.

00:15:50.640 --> 00:15:52.300
When was our last inspection?

00:15:53.720 --> 00:15:55.450
Are there any hardware issues?

00:15:56.160 --> 00:15:57.040
Okay, I got it.

00:15:58.840 --> 00:16:00.640
I might need to do an inspection.

00:16:00.760 --> 00:16:02.290
I'll confirm with you then.

00:16:02.560 --> 00:16:03.200
Okay.

00:16:16.160 --> 00:16:16.920
Hello, Director Zhang.

00:16:16.920 --> 00:16:17.520
Hello.

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:29.530
You aren't asleep, are you?

00:16:29.640 --> 00:16:30.520
How is it going?

00:16:31.480 --> 00:16:32.480
I'm almost done on my end.

00:16:32.480 --> 00:16:34.320
Have you found out the problem?

00:16:34.640 --> 00:16:35.880
I've tested it several times

00:16:35.880 --> 00:16:37.240
and ruled out other causes.

00:16:37.240 --> 00:16:39.720
I think it should be a hardware problem.

00:16:40.920 --> 00:16:41.920
You think?

00:16:43.200 --> 00:16:44.440
Is it or isn't it?

00:16:44.760 --> 00:16:45.520
It should be.

00:16:45.520 --> 00:16:47.250
What do you mean by "should be"?

00:16:48.360 --> 00:16:49.720
Isn't it a solution synthesis problem?

00:16:49.720 --> 00:16:50.360
No.

00:16:50.680 --> 00:16:52.440
What about spectrum synthesis?

00:16:52.440 --> 00:16:53.080
No.

00:16:53.640 --> 00:16:56.170
Does algorithm processing need adjustment?

00:16:56.400 --> 00:16:57.200
No.

00:16:57.680 --> 00:16:59.080
It's a hardware problem.

00:17:01.320 --> 00:17:02.980
I'll give you another chance.

00:17:03.000 --> 00:17:04.240
Think carefully.

00:17:04.400 --> 00:17:06.460
Where exactly did the problem occur?

00:17:07.200 --> 00:17:08.560
It is a hardware problem.

00:17:08.560 --> 00:17:09.290
Think again.

00:17:09.599 --> 00:17:11.440
Think again? What do you mean?

00:17:11.720 --> 00:17:13.450
I'm telling you to think again.

00:17:31.920 --> 00:17:33.320
It's a hardware problem.

00:17:33.360 --> 00:17:33.920
Are you sure?

00:17:33.920 --> 00:17:34.520
I'm sure.

00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:37.520
Why do I feel like you're not sure?

00:17:37.520 --> 00:17:38.840
No, I'm very sure.

00:17:38.840 --> 00:17:40.040
I am 200% sure.

00:17:40.040 --> 00:17:41.320
I'm very confident in my conclusion.

00:17:41.320 --> 00:17:42.520
It's a hardware problem.

00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:43.320
Zhang Ziming.

00:17:43.440 --> 00:17:44.920
If you suspect me instinctively

00:17:44.920 --> 00:17:46.760
and don't trust me, you don't have to use me.

00:17:46.760 --> 00:17:48.960
It's meaningless for us to be like this.

00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:54.440
I also checked it carefully myself.

00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:59.480
The conclusion is the same as yours.

00:18:00.440 --> 00:18:02.100
It is indeed a hardware issue.

00:18:02.360 --> 00:18:03.720
We'll gather early tomorrow morning.

00:18:03.720 --> 00:18:05.320
We'll go for another patrol.

00:18:06.720 --> 00:18:07.850
Rest early tonight.

00:18:16.080 --> 00:18:17.280
What do you mean?

00:18:26.240 --> 00:18:26.840
Old Yan.

00:18:31.240 --> 00:18:33.300
No, are you sure you want to wear that?

00:18:36.320 --> 00:18:37.720
Don't you have sneakers?

00:18:37.840 --> 00:18:39.900
No, my packages haven't arrived yet.

00:18:40.120 --> 00:18:41.120
Can't I wear this?

00:18:41.440 --> 00:18:43.280
It's not that you can't.

00:18:43.280 --> 00:18:45.520
It's just that we have to walk a lot today.

00:18:45.520 --> 00:18:47.720
I don't want to ruin your good shoes.

00:18:49.480 --> 00:18:50.640
Why don't you wear mine?

00:18:50.640 --> 00:18:51.640
I still have some.

00:18:51.960 --> 00:18:53.840
No need, my shoes are quite sturdy.

00:18:53.840 --> 00:18:54.680
Let's go.

00:18:56.000 --> 00:18:57.200
Okay, let's go.

00:19:31.400 --> 00:19:33.600
The readings and the circuits are fine.

00:19:34.480 --> 00:19:35.940
Let's head to the next one.

00:19:36.920 --> 00:19:38.040
Don't rush.

00:19:38.360 --> 00:19:40.490
Have something to eat and drink first.

00:19:44.800 --> 00:19:45.360
Here.

00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:46.240
Coming.

00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:51.020
At this time of day,

00:19:51.400 --> 00:19:52.930
the sun is at its strongest.

00:19:53.360 --> 00:19:54.160
It's hot,

00:19:54.840 --> 00:19:56.040
and the road is rough.

00:19:56.720 --> 00:19:59.440
The car can easily overheat.

00:20:00.160 --> 00:20:00.720
Here.

00:20:01.040 --> 00:20:02.480
I found that

00:20:02.480 --> 00:20:04.440
although the inspection work is tiring,

00:20:04.440 --> 00:20:05.400
it's quite interesting.

00:20:05.400 --> 00:20:06.200
Interesting?

00:20:08.160 --> 00:20:08.960
This is your first time,

00:20:08.960 --> 00:20:11.220
so of course you think it's interesting.

00:20:11.560 --> 00:20:14.080
We do the inspection on this route once a week.

00:20:14.080 --> 00:20:14.960
This area is covered

00:20:14.960 --> 00:20:17.440
with all kinds of base stations in different bands.

00:20:17.440 --> 00:20:19.200
It stretches for dozens of kilometers.

00:20:19.200 --> 00:20:20.480
Not counting the testing time,

00:20:20.480 --> 00:20:22.880
just driving to all the inspection points

00:20:22.880 --> 00:20:24.320
takes seven hours.

00:20:25.840 --> 00:20:28.100
Fifty-two weeks a year for over a decade,

00:20:29.080 --> 00:20:31.140
do you still think it's interesting?

00:20:41.200 --> 00:20:42.200
Look what this is.

00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:44.880
This looks like some kind of fossil.

00:20:44.880 --> 00:20:46.640
Is this a dinosaur egg fossil?

00:20:46.960 --> 00:20:49.080
How could a dinosaur egg be that small?

00:20:49.080 --> 00:20:50.010
What do you know?

00:20:50.200 --> 00:20:51.440
Many dinosaur egg fossils

00:20:51.440 --> 00:20:52.600
were discovered here.

00:20:52.600 --> 00:20:53.560
Ask Lao Yan if you don't believe me.

00:20:53.560 --> 00:20:54.120
Yes.

00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:56.850
We do have quite a few fossils here.

00:20:57.680 --> 00:20:58.960
But the one in your hand

00:20:58.960 --> 00:21:00.490
doesn't look like one to me.

00:21:00.920 --> 00:21:01.680
Whatever it is,

00:21:01.680 --> 00:21:03.740
let's take it back and study it first.

00:21:07.080 --> 00:21:08.140
There's more here.

00:21:31.320 --> 00:21:32.000
Mr. Yan.

00:21:32.760 --> 00:21:33.480
It broke.

00:21:34.640 --> 00:21:35.440
What broke?

00:21:36.440 --> 00:21:37.960
My shoe broke.

00:21:41.280 --> 00:21:43.040
It's an Italian brand.

00:21:44.160 --> 00:21:44.960
Okay, stop laughing.

00:21:44.960 --> 00:21:47.000
Do you have anything to glue it with?

00:21:47.960 --> 00:21:49.620
This is all I can do to help you.

00:21:50.480 --> 00:21:52.160
Alright, let's go.

00:21:52.160 --> 00:21:54.220
We must finish the inspection today.

00:22:18.920 --> 00:22:19.760
How is it?

00:22:21.320 --> 00:22:22.120
Not here.

00:22:26.560 --> 00:22:27.560
Is your foot okay?

00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:29.360
It's fine.

00:22:29.720 --> 00:22:30.640
Take mine if you need to.

00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:31.360
No thanks.

00:22:31.880 --> 00:22:32.940
I can still manage.

00:22:42.720 --> 00:22:43.400
Yan.

00:22:43.960 --> 00:22:46.280
We still have over ten inspection points left.

00:22:46.280 --> 00:22:47.560
At this pace...

00:22:47.560 --> 00:22:49.160
We definitely won't finish today.

00:22:49.160 --> 00:22:50.020
How about this?

00:22:50.400 --> 00:22:51.440
Let's split up.

00:22:52.160 --> 00:22:52.800
No.

00:22:53.880 --> 00:22:55.640
There's a rule for our outdoor inspection patrols.

00:22:55.640 --> 00:22:56.970
We must team up in pairs.

00:22:57.200 --> 00:22:58.730
If we separate, I'm worried

00:22:58.920 --> 00:23:00.050
what if... Alright.

00:23:00.800 --> 00:23:02.920
Special circumstances require special arrangements.

00:23:02.920 --> 00:23:04.840
Let's split into two groups.

00:23:05.240 --> 00:23:07.500
You guys handle the four on the east side.

00:23:08.040 --> 00:23:09.480
I'll take care of the ones on the west.

00:23:09.480 --> 00:23:10.200
No.

00:23:10.840 --> 00:23:12.320
The workload on the west side is too heavy.

00:23:12.320 --> 00:23:13.280
Give some to us.

00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:15.720
It's all dirt and gravel roads over there.

00:23:15.720 --> 00:23:16.980
It's too hard to drive.

00:23:17.160 --> 00:23:19.160
It might be easier if I just walk.

00:23:19.480 --> 00:23:20.540
It's settled then.

00:23:24.720 --> 00:23:25.520
No, Zhang.

00:23:27.520 --> 00:23:28.760
Before sunset,

00:23:28.960 --> 00:23:31.090
we must meet up at the gathering point.

00:23:31.760 --> 00:23:33.800
Contact me immediately if there are any problems.

00:23:33.800 --> 00:23:34.400
Keep in touch.

00:23:34.400 --> 00:23:35.080
Got it.

00:23:36.640 --> 00:23:37.500
Will that work?

00:23:40.720 --> 00:23:42.050
At the gathering point.

00:23:42.200 --> 00:23:42.880
Okay.

00:23:44.360 --> 00:23:45.120
Hurry up.

00:24:25.800 --> 00:24:28.040
These are the last few inspection points.

00:24:28.040 --> 00:24:29.840
If we still can't find the fault,

00:24:29.960 --> 00:24:33.220
it's not a problem with the power distribution equipment.

00:24:34.640 --> 00:24:35.840
The voltage is wrong.

00:24:36.120 --> 00:24:38.250
The test signal feedback is all noise.

00:24:39.680 --> 00:24:40.610
What's going on?

00:24:42.480 --> 00:24:43.680
Where is the problem?

00:25:12.800 --> 00:25:13.530
As expected.

00:25:15.400 --> 00:25:16.530
The line is damaged.

00:25:17.680 --> 00:25:19.080
This is going to be tough.

00:25:20.760 --> 00:25:22.600
This was bitten by an animal.

00:25:23.320 --> 00:25:24.450
What kind of animal?

00:25:24.800 --> 00:25:25.520
A wolf.

00:25:26.640 --> 00:25:27.280
A wolf.

00:25:27.680 --> 00:25:28.940
There are wolves here?

00:25:30.400 --> 00:25:31.660
There weren't before.

00:25:31.880 --> 00:25:34.320
The environment has improved these past few years,

00:25:34.320 --> 00:25:35.920
so the wolves have come back.

00:25:36.640 --> 00:25:38.300
We won't run into one, will we?

00:25:39.400 --> 00:25:41.080
Never mind running into wolves,

00:25:41.080 --> 00:25:42.880
we can't even stand a sandstorm.

00:25:43.480 --> 00:25:44.800
Come on, hurry.

00:25:45.560 --> 00:25:47.880
Let's replace this line.

00:26:01.600 --> 00:26:03.800
Speak of the devil, the wolves are here.

00:26:05.080 --> 00:26:05.520
But that sound,

00:26:05.520 --> 00:26:07.920
it seems to be coming from Lao Zhang's side.

00:26:08.960 --> 00:26:11.520
Go get him. I can handle this.

00:26:12.320 --> 00:26:13.600
With those worn-out shoes of his,

00:26:13.600 --> 00:26:15.080
he couldn't run even if he met a wolf.

00:26:15.080 --> 00:26:16.760
Okay, then hurry up.

00:26:17.320 --> 00:26:17.960
Later,

00:26:19.320 --> 00:26:20.720
don't forget to regroup.

00:26:21.560 --> 00:26:22.440
At the meeting point, right?

00:26:22.440 --> 00:26:23.320
Right, the meeting point.

00:26:23.320 --> 00:26:23.960
Listen,

00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:26.140
wait for us. Don't wander off.

00:27:33.320 --> 00:27:36.640
Lao Zhang.

00:27:36.800 --> 00:27:37.640
Lao Yan.

00:27:37.960 --> 00:27:39.760
Why are you here? Where is Wu Wei?

00:27:42.040 --> 00:27:43.440
I found the problem.

00:27:44.160 --> 00:27:46.040
It's the distribution box and the wiring.

00:27:46.040 --> 00:27:47.500
He's fixing it over there.

00:27:48.320 --> 00:27:49.640
I just heard a wolf howl.

00:27:49.640 --> 00:27:50.720
We heard it too.

00:27:50.720 --> 00:27:52.000
There really are wolves.

00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:53.000
Wolves aren't scary.

00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:54.320
What's scary is the sandstorm.

00:27:54.320 --> 00:27:55.800
Hurry up and pack your things. Follow me.

00:27:55.800 --> 00:27:57.080
Let's go. Follow me.

00:27:59.240 --> 00:28:01.240
It's locked. Anything else?

00:28:02.080 --> 00:28:02.800
Wu Wei.

00:28:02.800 --> 00:28:04.840
Please respond, Wu Wei.

00:28:13.560 --> 00:28:14.200
Wu Wei.

00:28:14.200 --> 00:28:15.530
Please respond, Wu Wei.

00:28:17.840 --> 00:28:18.400
Wu Wei.

00:28:18.400 --> 00:28:19.730
Please respond, Wu Wei.

00:28:23.320 --> 00:28:25.400
Wu Wei, please respond.

00:28:27.560 --> 00:28:29.000
Oh no. No signal.

00:28:29.960 --> 00:28:31.560
Can you contact the station?

00:28:56.280 --> 00:28:57.000
No signal.

00:28:57.000 --> 00:28:57.800
What should we do?

00:28:57.800 --> 00:28:59.530
We can't leave him there alone.

00:29:01.640 --> 00:29:02.370
Don't panic.

00:29:04.080 --> 00:29:05.200
If the station

00:29:05.200 --> 00:29:07.130
can't reach us, they'll find a way.

00:29:07.680 --> 00:29:09.320
Let's go meet up with him first.

00:29:09.320 --> 00:29:09.960
Let's go.

00:29:53.320 --> 00:29:54.280
Kashgar said

00:29:54.400 --> 00:29:55.880
Mr. Zhang, Wu Wei, and the others went out for an inspection.

00:29:55.880 --> 00:29:57.120
They encountered a sandstorm and lost contact.

00:29:57.120 --> 00:29:57.920
A sandstorm?

00:30:01.120 --> 00:30:02.180
Does Beijing know?

00:30:02.720 --> 00:30:03.920
They probably do.

00:30:14.040 --> 00:30:14.920
Sorry,

00:30:14.920 --> 00:30:17.720
the number you dialed is out of service.

00:31:33.800 --> 00:31:34.660
What happened?

00:31:34.800 --> 00:31:35.640
It's stuck.

00:31:36.360 --> 00:31:36.920
Come on.

00:31:49.800 --> 00:31:50.400
Yan.

00:31:50.880 --> 00:31:51.880
I'll push, you go.

00:31:51.880 --> 00:31:52.480
Come on.

00:31:55.720 --> 00:31:56.320
Come on.

00:32:08.920 --> 00:32:09.840
Yan! Zhang!

00:32:11.080 --> 00:32:12.920
I've arrived at the assembly point.

00:32:12.920 --> 00:32:14.320
Please reply if you copy.

00:32:15.880 --> 00:32:17.480
Please reply if you copy.

00:32:18.760 --> 00:32:19.520
Two,

00:32:19.520 --> 00:32:19.960
three!

00:32:19.960 --> 00:32:21.440
One, two, three!

00:32:26.200 --> 00:32:27.120
Two, three!

00:32:27.320 --> 00:32:28.240
This is Wu Wei.

00:32:29.120 --> 00:32:29.960
I've arrived at the assembly point.

00:32:29.960 --> 00:32:30.880
Where are you?

00:32:31.120 --> 00:32:32.520
Please reply if you copy.

00:32:33.840 --> 00:32:34.680
Please reply if you copy.

00:32:34.680 --> 00:32:35.600
Zhang! Yan!

00:32:47.440 --> 00:32:48.080
Yan,

00:32:49.120 --> 00:32:50.080
this won't work.

00:32:50.560 --> 00:32:52.420
You stay here and wait for rescue.

00:32:52.440 --> 00:32:53.700
I'll go look for Wu Wei.

00:32:54.080 --> 00:32:54.720
What for?

00:32:54.920 --> 00:32:56.250
To get killed one by one?

00:32:56.400 --> 00:32:57.800
I brought him here,

00:32:57.800 --> 00:32:58.880
so I have to take him back.

00:32:58.880 --> 00:33:00.080
I'm responsible for him.

00:33:00.080 --> 00:33:01.720
Let me tell you, Zhang Ziming,

00:33:01.720 --> 00:33:04.320
you have to listen to me during the inspection.

00:33:04.800 --> 00:33:06.040
At a time like this,

00:33:06.280 --> 00:33:08.080
we absolutely cannot separate.

00:33:21.960 --> 00:33:24.000
Haven't you contacted Mr. Zhang and Wu Wei yet?

00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:24.480
No.

00:33:24.800 --> 00:33:26.560
Mr. Qin and Mr. Gu are both trying to figure out a way.

00:33:26.560 --> 00:33:28.160
Keep us updated in the group.

00:33:28.440 --> 00:33:29.040
Okay.

00:33:47.120 --> 00:33:48.120
Hello, Nannan.

00:33:49.200 --> 00:33:50.460
What's the situation?

00:33:50.880 --> 00:33:52.280
What happened to Wu Wei?

00:33:52.480 --> 00:33:54.200
He encountered a sandstorm while checking the lines.

00:33:54.200 --> 00:33:56.530
He's been out of contact for two hours now.

00:33:56.560 --> 00:33:58.320
All three of them are unreachable.

00:33:58.320 --> 00:34:00.040
Beijing has contacted Kashgar immediately

00:34:00.040 --> 00:34:01.680
to discuss emergency search plans.

00:34:01.680 --> 00:34:04.210
Ying Ziqi is also trying to send them a signal.

00:34:04.760 --> 00:34:07.000
We are also discussing if there are any other plans.

00:34:07.000 --> 00:34:08.880
Jia, we are all waiting for news.

00:34:09.440 --> 00:34:10.360
Don't worry.

00:34:12.760 --> 00:34:13.400
Jia.

00:34:13.400 --> 00:34:14.239
Communication is cut off.

00:34:14.239 --> 00:34:16.239
No signal for phones or walkie-talkies.

00:34:16.239 --> 00:34:17.639
We can't contact anyone.

00:34:18.159 --> 00:34:19.480
How could this happen?

00:34:20.239 --> 00:34:21.920
Have you contacted the rescue team?

00:34:21.920 --> 00:34:24.650
Kashgar said they are already figuring out a way.

00:34:24.760 --> 00:34:25.440
Jia.

00:34:26.480 --> 00:34:27.639
Don't overthink it.

00:34:27.840 --> 00:34:28.960
They will be fine.

00:34:29.560 --> 00:34:30.719
Listen to me.

00:34:30.840 --> 00:34:32.280
If there are any problems or news,

00:34:32.280 --> 00:34:32.960
update us immediately.

00:34:32.960 --> 00:34:33.760
Do you hear me?

00:34:33.920 --> 00:34:34.480
Okay.

00:35:22.960 --> 00:35:24.840
We have contacted Kashgar.

00:35:24.840 --> 00:35:27.100
They are trying to send reinforcements.

00:35:27.520 --> 00:35:30.400
It happened so suddenly. It's below freezing at night there,

00:35:30.400 --> 00:35:32.400
and they don't have winter clothes.

00:35:33.400 --> 00:35:34.080
Jiajia.

00:35:36.480 --> 00:35:37.960
They will be fine.

00:35:39.320 --> 00:35:40.960
If there's any update on my end,

00:35:40.960 --> 00:35:42.760
I will let you know immediately.

00:35:43.560 --> 00:35:44.200
Okay.

00:35:49.480 --> 00:35:52.800
If we can't find them tonight...

00:35:54.760 --> 00:35:56.620
The situation is not optimistic.

00:36:12.560 --> 00:36:14.400
One, two, three.

00:36:16.320 --> 00:36:18.440
One, two, three.

00:36:18.880 --> 00:36:19.760
Come on.

00:36:26.960 --> 00:36:28.120
One, two, three.

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:29.640
Come on.

00:36:30.560 --> 00:36:31.200
Come on.

00:36:37.280 --> 00:36:38.080
Get in the car.

00:36:42.280 --> 00:36:43.080
Sorry,

00:36:43.080 --> 00:36:45.920
the number you dialed is out of service.

00:36:45.920 --> 00:36:47.480
Please try again later.

00:37:25.360 --> 00:37:27.440
Wu Wei, have your coordinates changed?

00:37:27.440 --> 00:37:29.640
We've already sent someone to find you.

00:37:33.640 --> 00:37:35.160
Wu Wei, you must hold on.

00:37:35.960 --> 00:37:37.480
Find a place out of the wind.

00:37:37.480 --> 00:37:39.540
Don't get hypothermia, understand?

00:38:15.040 --> 00:38:15.880
Jia.

00:38:17.240 --> 00:38:19.440
I might not make it this time.

00:38:20.800 --> 00:38:23.600
I'm afraid I'll never see you again.

00:38:25.080 --> 00:38:27.140
There's something I want to tell you.

00:38:28.280 --> 00:38:30.240
I've actually always liked you.

00:38:46.600 --> 00:38:47.240
Wu Wei.

00:38:48.160 --> 00:38:50.290
Did you forget what you said last time?

00:38:51.440 --> 00:38:52.480
You said

00:38:53.040 --> 00:38:54.840
in your flight path,

00:38:55.480 --> 00:38:58.080
I've always been the most critical parameter.

00:38:58.280 --> 00:39:00.480
But you have to come back and keep flying

00:39:00.760 --> 00:39:03.280
for this parameter to be useful!

00:40:39.960 --> 00:40:41.440
Wu Wei, how are you?

00:40:43.160 --> 00:40:43.960
Wu Wei,

00:40:43.960 --> 00:40:45.280
you must keep warm.

00:40:45.640 --> 00:40:47.900
Let me know you're safe when you get this.

00:40:49.520 --> 00:40:50.120
Mr. Qin.

00:40:50.120 --> 00:40:51.680
You are quite lucky, kid.

00:40:51.680 --> 00:40:52.360
I'm fine.

00:40:52.520 --> 00:40:53.850
You got lucky this time.

00:40:54.280 --> 00:40:55.840
Be more careful on future missions.

00:40:55.840 --> 00:40:57.370
Sorry for making you worry.

00:40:58.280 --> 00:40:59.160
I'm fine.

00:40:59.720 --> 00:41:01.280
It doesn't matter if I worry.

00:41:01.280 --> 00:41:03.010
You should let Chu Jiajia know.

00:41:03.280 --> 00:41:04.080
Hurry up.

00:41:04.560 --> 00:41:05.320
Don't worry.

00:41:05.680 --> 00:41:07.520
She is very worried about you.

00:41:13.840 --> 00:41:15.520
Wu Wei, you have to hold on.

00:41:15.520 --> 00:41:16.980
Please don't fall asleep.

00:41:18.680 --> 00:41:20.880
Don't forget what you told me last time.

00:41:20.920 --> 00:41:23.280
You said that in your flight trajectory,

00:41:23.280 --> 00:41:25.810
I have long been the most critical parameter.

00:41:26.400 --> 00:41:27.160
Wu Wei.

00:41:27.400 --> 00:41:28.960
You must come back alive.

00:41:29.280 --> 00:41:30.240
This is an order.

00:42:00.600 --> 00:42:01.460
Did you save it?

00:42:01.840 --> 00:42:02.720
Keep it safe.

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:04.840
It almost became my memorial portrait.

00:42:04.840 --> 00:42:06.000
I'm fine, Jia.

00:42:06.560 --> 00:42:07.490
I'm doing great.

00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:09.920
Don't worry or be sad.

00:42:11.720 --> 00:42:14.160
I'm a little sad, just a little.

00:42:14.760 --> 00:42:16.200
Then I would be sad.

00:42:16.320 --> 00:42:17.400
After all, when I opened my eyes,

00:42:17.400 --> 00:42:19.460
the first person I thought of was you.

00:42:34.760 --> 00:42:35.560
You're awake.

00:42:37.120 --> 00:42:38.050
Are you alright?

00:42:38.120 --> 00:42:39.180
You should be glad.

00:42:39.840 --> 00:42:41.160
You almost

00:42:41.160 --> 00:42:43.040
lost your life in the Gobi Desert.

00:42:43.280 --> 00:42:44.280
Drink some water.

00:42:45.920 --> 00:42:47.040
Is your foot okay?

00:42:47.960 --> 00:42:48.960
My foot is fine.

00:42:49.520 --> 00:42:50.520
I'm fine too.

00:42:51.200 --> 00:42:52.530
But my shoes are ruined.

00:42:53.560 --> 00:42:55.490
I made a major discovery this time.

00:43:00.760 --> 00:43:03.640
The spacecraft names and related missions in this series are fictionalized.

